 around 25% of the active population.  Lastly, the services sector contributes 68.3% to the GDP and employs 65.8% of the active population. The information technology and communications sectors are the most important contributors to the GDP.}}</ref>}}\n|poverty             = {{plainlist|\n*21.9% \u2013 income below  \u20ac300/month (2018)<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.compareyourincome.org |title = Compare your income - Perception of income inequality in OECD countries}}</ref>\n*{{decreasePositive}} 28.3% at risk of poverty (2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/tgm/refreshTableAction.do?tab=table&plugin=1&pcode=t2020_50&language=en |title=People at risk of poverty or social exclusion |publisher=[[Eurostat]] |website=ec.europa.eu/eurostat |access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref>}}\n|labor               = {{plainlist|\n*{{decrease}} 1,439,700 (2019)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SL.TLF.TOTL.IN?locations=LT&most_recent_value_desc=true |title=Labor force, total \u2013 Lithuania |publisher=[[World Bank]] |website=data.worldbank.org |access-date=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n*{{increase}} 77.8% employment rate (Target: 72.8%; 2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/tgm/table.do?tab=table&init=1&language=en&pcode=t2020_10&plugin=1 |title=Employment rate by sex, age group 20\u201364 |publisher=[[Eurostat]] |website=ec.europa.eu/eurostat |access-date=18 June 2019}}</ref>}}\n|gini                = {{decreasePositive}} 36.9 {{color|darkorange|medium}} (2018, [[Eurostat]])<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/tgm/table.do?tab=table&init=1&language=en&pcode=tessi190&plugin=1 |title=Gini coefficient of equivalised disposable income \u2013 EU-SILC survey |publisher=[[Eurostat]] |website=ec.europa.eu |access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n|hdi                 = {{plainlist|\n*{{increase}} 0.869 {{color|darkgreen|very high}} (2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hdr.undp.org/en/indicators/137506 |title=Human Developm